NAME
     errstop - Terminates the error-logging daemon

SYNOPSIS
     errstop [namelist]

DESCRIPTION
   Purpose
     Only the super-user can use errstop.  The error-logging
     daemon errdemon(1M) is terminated by using errstop.  This
     task is accomplished by executing ps(1) to determine the
     daemon's identity and then sending it a software kill signal
     with signal(2).

   System Name List:
     Enter the path name of the system.  Default is /unix.

SEE ALSO
     errdemon(1M), kill(2), ps(1).


